                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/611.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Special
                        Agent <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consul, Mazatlan, reports Mazatlan Water Works confiscated May 24. Reported
                    Electric Company will be confiscated near future. Americans interested these
                    companies. Make vigorous protest to General Carranza against confiscation these
                    properties and request him order restoration water works.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
